{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8f2ce99f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2054"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2054"},"text":"§ 2054.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Statement of purpose","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The purpose of this subchapter is to promote better relations and understanding between the United States and the nations of Asia and the Pacific (hereinafter referred to as “the East”) through cooperative study, training, and research, by establishing in Hawaii a Center for Cultural and Technical Interchange Between East and West where scholars and students in various fields from the nations of the East and West may study, give and receive training, exchange ideas and views, and conduct other activities primarily in support of the objectives of the United States Information and Educational Exchange Act of 1948, as amended [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1431"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 1431","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], title III of chapter II of the Mutual Security Act of 1954, and other Acts promoting the international, educational, cultural, and related activities of the United States."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8f2ce9a0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/472"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–472","children":[],"tail":", ch. VII, § 702, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/141"},"text":"74 Stat. 141","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8f2ce9a1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8f2ce9a2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id8f2ce9a3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The United States Information and Educational Exchange Act of 1948, as amended, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-01-27/ch36"},"text":"act Jan. 27, 1948, ch. 36","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/6"},"text":"62 Stat. 6","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 18 (§ 1431 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1431"},"text":"section 1431 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Mutual Security Act of 1954, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-26/ch937"},"text":"act Aug. 26, 1954, ch. 937","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/832"},"text":"68 Stat. 832","children":[],"tail":", as amended by acts "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-07-08/ch301"},"text":"July 8, 1955, ch. 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/283"},"text":"69 Stat. 283","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-07-18/ch627"},"text":"July 18, 1956, ch. 627","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2 to 11, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/555"},"text":"70 Stat. 555","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1957-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1957","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–141","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/71/355"},"text":"71 Stat. 355","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/477"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–477","children":[],"tail":", ch. 1, §§ 101 to 103, ch. II, §§ 201 to 205, ch. III, § 301, ch. IV, § 401, ch. V, § 501, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/261"},"text":"72 Stat. 261","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-07-24"},"text":"July 24, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/108/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–108, § 2","children":[],"tail":", ch. 1, § 101, ch. II, §§ 201 to 205(a) to (i), (k) to (n), ch. III, § 301, ch. IV, § 401(a) to (k), (m), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/246"},"text":"73 Stat. 246","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/472"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–472","children":[],"tail":", ch. I to V, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/134"},"text":"74 Stat. 134","children":[],"tail":". Title III of chapter II of the Act was classified to sections 1891 to 1896, 1897, and 1898 of this title and was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", pt. III, § 642(a)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-04"},"text":"Sept. 4, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/460"},"text":"75 Stat. 460","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/472"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–472","children":[],"tail":", ch. II, § 203(d), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/136"},"text":"74 Stat. 136","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1754"},"text":"section 1754 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8f2ce9a4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id8f2ce9a5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/472"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–472","children":[],"tail":", ch. VII, § 701, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/141"},"text":"74 Stat. 141","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/86/472"},"text":"“This chapter [enacting this subchapter] may be cited as the ‘Center for Cultural and Technical Interchange Between East and West Act of 1960’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id8f2ce9a6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents and Statutory Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id8f2ce9a7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All functions vested in the President, the Secretary of State, the Department of State, the United States Information Agency, or the Director thereof, under this chapter, were transferred to the Director of the International Communication Agency by Reorg. Plan No. 2 of 1977, § 7(a)(7), 42 F.R. 62461, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1637"},"text":"91 Stat. 1637","children":[],"tail":", set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1461"},"text":"section 1461 of this title","children":[],"tail":", effective on or before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1978","children":[],"tail":", at such time as specified by the President. The International Communication Agency, and the Director thereof, were redesignated the United States Information Agency, and the Director thereof, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/241/s303"},"text":"section 303 of Pub. L. 97–241","children":[],"tail":", title III, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-08-24"},"text":"Aug. 24, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/291"},"text":"96 Stat. 291","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1461"},"text":"section 1461 of this title","children":[],"tail":". United States Information Agency (other than Broadcasting Board of Governors and International Broadcasting Bureau) abolished and functions transferred to Secretary of State, see sections 6531 and 6532 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
